        "excerpt": "Name     Tier     Type                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Far Shot                  Novice                                                                            Hunt Prey                  Novice                                                                                                    Hunter's Aim                  Novice                                                                                                    Camouflage                  Veteran                                                                            Deadly Aim                  Veteran                                                                                                    Debilitating Shot                  Veteran                                                                                                    Incredible Ricochet                  Veteran                                                                                                    Double Prey                  Master                                                                            Legendary Shot                  Epic                                                                            Shadow Hunter                  Epic                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Far Shot              Novice                        Your experience in the field has taught you how to focus your aim at a distance, increasing your accuracy. Double your weapons’ range increments.                                  Hunt Prey                              Novice                                       Concentrate                                                      Duration           24 hours, or until you use this power again                                  You designate a single creature as your prey and focus your attacks against that creature. You must be able to see or hear the prey, or you must be tracking the prey during exploration. You gain a +2 bonus to Perception rolls or Survival rolls made to Seek or Track your prey. You also ignore the penalty for making ranged attacks within your second increment against the prey you’re hunting. The first time you hit your hunted prey in a round, you also deal 1d8 additional precision damage.                                  Hunter's Aim                              Novice                                       Concentrate                                 By spending a moment to focus, you can ensure your attack strikes true. Make a ranged weapon Strike. On this Strike, you gain a +2 bonus to the attack roll and ignore the target’s concealed condition.                                  Camouflage              Veteran                        You alter your appearance to blend in to your surroundings. While outdoors, you can Sneak even if you’re observed.                                  Deadly Aim                              Veteran                                       Open                                 You aim for your prey’s weak spots, making your shot more challenging but dealing more damage if you hit. Make a ranged Strike against your hunted prey at a -2 penalty. Your Strike’s damage increases by 2 + Prof.                                  Debilitating Shot                              Veteran                                       Flourish                                 Aiming for a weak point, you impede your foe with a precise shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike. If it hits and deals damage, the target is slowed 1 until the end of its next turn.                                  Incredible Ricochet                              Veteran                                       Concentrate                    Press                                 After your first shot singles out your opponent’s position, you direct another that ricochets around obstacles and strikes unerringly. Make a ranged weapon Strike. You ignore the target’s concealed condition and all cover.                                  Double Prey              Master                                             Prerequisites           Hunt Prey                                  You can focus on two foes at once, hunting both of them down. When you use the Hunt Prey power, you can pick two creatures as your prey.                                  Legendary Shot              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Far Shot, Hunt Prey                                  Your focus on your hunted prey, perceiving angles, air resistance, and every variable that would affect your ranged attack. You can ignore the penalty for attacking up to five range increments away when attacking your hunted prey.                                  Shadow Hunter              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Camouflage                                  You blend in to your surroundings so well that others have trouble telling you apart from the terrain. While outdoors, you’re always concealed from all foes if you choose to be.",
